  "narrative_arc": "Young Latina girl who wants a house of her own — not the crumbling house on Mango Street. Cisneros renders the neighborhood with poetic precision: every house, every family, every yard. Esperanza maps her world through architecture — houses as destiny, houses as identity, houses as escape.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Esperanza fills Layer 5 (Housing) with the experiential dimension no data can capture — what it feels like to be ashamed of where you live. Her dome links housing shame to identity formation to creative ambition.",
